                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17790217-22-off120 t17790217-22-cd121"></join>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17790217-22-person238">
                  JOHN
                   ROBINS
               <interp inst="t17790217-22-person238" type="surname" value="ROBINS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17790217-22-person238" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17790217-22-person238" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I belong to the Custom-house. It is my duty some times to go to the upper station to examine goods; I went there on the morning of the 13th of January; when I came there I missed my handkerchief; a waterman came to me and asked me if I had lost my handkerchief; I said I had; he said he saw two chaps following me in <placeName id="t17790217-22-crimeloc122">Thames-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17790217-22-crimeloc122" type="placeName" value="Thames-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17790217-22-crimeloc122" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17790217-22-off120 t17790217-22-crimeloc122"></join>; a gentleman in the office offered to lay a trap for them; he went out up Thames-street, with his handkerchief hanging out of his pocket; I followed him; they<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="177902170018"></xptr> seeing his handkerchief out of his pocket went after him; upon which they were seised and my handkerchief was found upon Daniel.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17790217-22-person239">
                  THOMAS
                   WARD
               <interp inst="t17790217-22-person239" type="surname" value="WARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17790217-22-person239" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17790217-22-person239" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I was charged with the prisoners. I searched Daniel, and found this handkerchief upon him.</p>
               <p>(The handkerchief was produced in court, and deposed to by the prosecutor.)</p>
               <p>DANIEL's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I found the handkerchief in a bundle under a gateway in Thames-street.</p>
               <p>(There being nothing to affect Levi, he was not put on his defence.)</p>
               <p>DANIEL <rs id="t17790217-22-verdict123" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17790217-22-verdict123" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
